---
Promote a run receipt to become the new baseline.

This command copies a run receipt to a baseline location, optionally normalizing run-specific fields (run_id, timestamps) to make baselines more stable across runs. Typically used on trusted branches (e.g., main) after successful benchmark runs.

Exit codes: 0 for success, 1 for errors.

Usage: perfgate promote [OPTIONS] --current <CURRENT>

Options:
      --current <CURRENT> Path or cloud URI to the current run receipt to promote

      --to <TO> Path or cloud URI where the baseline should be written

      --to-server Promote to the baseline server instead of a local file

      --benchmark <BENCHMARK> Benchmark name for server promotion (required with --to-server)

      --promote-project <PROMOTE_PROJECT> Project name for server promotion (overrides global --project flag)

      --version <VERSION> Version identifier for the promoted baseline (server only)

      --normalize Strip run-specific fields (run_id, timestamps) for stable baselines

      --pretty Pretty-print JSON

      --ratchet Enable budget ratcheting on local promote path (never for --to-server)

      --compare <COMPARE> Compare receipt providing trustworthy evidence for ratcheting

      --config <CONFIG> Config file to update when --ratchet is enabled [default: perfgate.toml]

      --ratchet-out <RATCHET_OUT> Output path for machine-readable ratchet artifact [default: perfgate.ratchet.v1.json]

  -h, --help Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Global Options:
      --baseline-server <BASELINE_SERVER> URL of the baseline server (e.g., http://localhost:3000/api/v1) Can also be set via PERFGATE_SERVER_URL environment variable

      --api-key <API_KEY> API key for authentication with the baseline server. Can also be set via PERFGATE_API_KEY environment variable

      --project <PROJECT> Project name for multi-tenancy. Can also be set via PERFGATE_PROJECT environment variable
